Tidy methods for wbgee models

Source: R/asym_gee.R, R/wb_gee.R
wbgee_tidiers.Rd

panelr provides methods to access wbgee data in a tidy format

Usage

# S3 method for asym_gee
tidy(x, conf.int = FALSE, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

# S3 method for wbgee
tidy(x, conf.int = FALSE, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

# S3 method for wbgee
glance(x, ...)

Arguments

x

A wbgee object.

conf.int

Logical indicating whether or not to include a confidence interval in the tidied output. Defaults to FALSE.

conf.level

The confidence level to use for the confidence interval if conf.int = TRUE. Must be strictly greater than 0 and less than 1. Defaults to 0.95, which corresponds to a 95 percent confidence interval.

...

Ignored

Examples

data("WageData")
wages <- panel_data(WageData, id = id, wave = t)
model <- wbgee(lwage ~ lag(union) + wks, data = wages)
if (requireNamespace("generics")) {
  generics::tidy(model)
}
